net.vivialconnect.model.log

Class Log

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.vivialconnect.model.VivialConnectResource
      • net.vivialconnect.model.log.Log
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Log
extends VivialConnectResource
    This class holds Vivial Connect logs a variety of events.

    Use the logs resources to pull information from our logs relating to your account activity. Access aggregated logs to view information about log activity over time.

    For more info, visit Logs

      • getLogs

        public static LogCollection getLogs(Date startTime,
                                    Date endTime,
                                    Map<String,String> queryParameters)
                             throws ForbiddenAccessException,
                                    BadRequestException,
                                    UnauthorizedAccessException,
                                    ServerErrorException,
                                    ApiRequestException
        Search and filter for all logs relating to your account activity.

        StartTime and endTime should be formated in ISO 8601 format like YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ.

        Parameters:
        startTime - start date and time in ISO 8601 format like YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ
        endTime - end date and time in ISO 8601 format like YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ
        queryParameters - a map of String key-value pairs used to filter results, possible values are:

        log_type – The log type as a string. Log-types are typically of the form ITEM_TYPE.ACTION, where ITEM_TYPE is the type of item that was affected and ACTION is what happened to it. For example: message.queued.

        item_id – Unique id of item that was affected.

        operator_id – Unique id of operator that caused this log.

        limit – Used for pagination: number of log records to return. Maximum value: 150.

        start_key – Used for pagination: value of last_key from previous response

        Returns:
        a list of log collection
        Throws:
        ForbiddenAccessException - if the user does not have permission to the API resource
        BadRequestException - if the request params and/or payload are not valid
        UnauthorizedAccessException - if any of the auth properties account ID, API Key and/or API secret are not valid
        ServerErrorException - if the server is unable to process the request
        ApiRequestException - if an API error occurs
        See Also:
        getLogs(Date, Date)

        Search and filter the list of aggregated logs in your account.

        Use aggregated logs to view information about log activity over time.

        Parameters:
        startTime - start date and time in ISO 8601 format like YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ
        endTime - end date and time in ISO 8601 format like YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ
        aggregatorType - valid values are: minutes, hours, days, months, years
        queryParameters - a map of String key-value pairs used to filter results, possible values are:

        log_type – The log type as a string. Log-types are typically of the form ITEM_TYPE.ACTION, where ITEM_TYPE is the type of item that was affected and ACTION is what happened to it. For example: message.queued.

        operator_id – Unique id of operator that caused this log.

        limit – Used for pagination. Number of log records to return. Maximum value: 150.

        start_key – Used for pagination. Value of last_key from previous response

        Returns:
        a list of log collection
        Throws:
        ForbiddenAccessException - if the user does not have permission to the API resource
        BadRequestException - if the request params and/or payload are not valid
        UnauthorizedAccessException - if any of the auth properties account ID, API Key and/or API secret are not valid
        ServerErrorException - if the server is unable to process the request
        ApiRequestException - if an API error occurs
